538/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Solitary+fibrous+tumour+and+haemangiopericytoma%3A+evolution+of+a+concept&amp;author=C+Gengler&amp;author=L+Guillou&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;journal=Histopathology&amp;pages=63-74&amp;doi=10.1111%2Fj.1365-2559.2005.02290.x&amp;pmid=16359538">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">40.</div><div id="r40" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Wat SY, Sur M, Dhamanaskar K. Solitary fibrous tumor (SFT) of the pelvis. <em>Clin Imaging</em> 2008; 32(2):152–156.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.clinimag.2007.07.003">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18313582/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Solitary+fibrous+tumor+%28SFT%29+of+the+pelvis&amp;author=SY+Wat&amp;author=M+Sur&amp;author=K+Dhamanaskar&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=Clin+Imaging&amp;pages=152-156&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.clinimag.2007.07.003&amp;pmid=18313582">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">41.</div><div id="r41" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Narla LD, Newman B, Spottswood SS, Narla S, Kolli R. Inflammatory pseudotumor. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2003;23(3):719–729.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.233025073">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12740472/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Inflammatory+pseudotumor&amp;author=LD+Narla&amp;author=B+Newman&amp;author=SS+Spottswood&amp;author=S